This extension hides the system clock in the top center of the panel of Kali Linux

Working in gnome 3.20.3(kali 2, 2016.2)

# How to hide the clock 

1. Create the Hide_Clock@jechoi directory and copy metadata.json, extension.js in it

  # mkdir ~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions
  # cd ~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions
  # mkdir Hide_Clock@jechoi
  # cd Hide_Clock@jechoi

2. Run Tweak Tool and enable the extension in the Extensions tab
